  "prompt": "Can someone give me the datasheet for TEG?",
  "response": "I'm unable to provide the complete datasheet for a TEG (Thermoelectric Generator) directly. However, I can help you find it! Here's how you can obtain the datasheet:\n\n1. **Identify the Specific TEG Model and Manufacturer:**\n   - TEGs are produced by various manufacturers, each with different specifications and models. Ensure you know the exact model number and the company that manufactures it.\n\n2. **Visit the Manufacturer\u2019s Official Website:**\n   - Once you've identified the manufacturer, go to their official website. Companies often have dedicated sections for their products.\n\n3. **Navigate to the Product Page:**\n   - Find the specific TEG product you're interested in. This is usually under sections like \"Products,\" \"Thermoelectric Generators,\" or similar categories.\n\n4. **Look for a 'Downloads' or 'Resources' Section:**\n   - Manufacturers typically provide datasheets, user manuals, and other technical documents in these sections. Look for links labeled \"Datasheet,\" \"Technical Specifications,\" or \"Product Documentation.\"\n\n5. **Contact Customer Support if Needed:**\n   - If you can't find the datasheet on the website, consider reaching out to the company's customer support or sales team. They can often provide the necessary documents directly.\n\n**Example Manufacturers of TEGs:**\n- **Ferrotec:** [Ferrotec TEG Products](https://www.ferrotec.com/products/thermoelectric-generators/)\n- **Hi-Z Technology:** [Hi-Z Thermoelectric Generators](https://hi-z.com/thermoelectric-generators)\n- **Tegpro:** [Tegpro Products](https://tegpro.com/products/)\n\nIf you provide more specific information about the TEG you're interested in, such as the manufacturer or model number, I can offer more targeted assistance!",
